e, "description": "Problems and improvements with respect to compile times."}, {"id": 211668100, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWwyMTE2NjgxMDA=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/T-compiler", "name": "T-compiler", "color": "bfd4f2", "default": false, "description": "Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue."}, {"id": 900795185, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWw5MDA3OTUxODU=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/A-const-eval", "name": "A-const-eval", "color": "f7e101", "default": false, "description": "Area: constant evaluation (mir interpretation)"}], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 8, "created_at": "2020-04-25T21:18:13Z", "updated_at": "2020-04-27T15:02:22Z", "closed_at": "2020-04-27T15:02:22Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "It's very common to use static arrays in C/C++ when doing Competitive Programming like so:\r\n```C++\r\nconst int SIZE = 1e4 + 10;\r\nconst int STATES = 1e3 + 10;\r\nint dp[SIZE][STATES];\r\n```\r\nI tried the same technique in Rust to save some time at runtime, but there was a problem. Program became compiling too long. From 1-2 seconds using vectors to 30-60 seconds using static memory. Even judge server returned `Compilation timeout` error. Here is same code in Rust:\r\n\r\n```Rust\r\nconst SIZE: usize = 10010;\r\nconst STATES: usize = 1010;\r\nstatic mut dp: [[bool; STATES]; SIZE] = [[false; STATES]; SIZE];\r\n```\r\nReplacing this code with:\r\n```Rust\r\nlet mut dp: Vec<Vec<bool>> = vec![vec![false; STATES]; SIZE];\r\n```\r\nnow it compiles 1-2 seconds.", "closed_by": {"login": "oli-obk", "id": 332036, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjMzMjAzNg==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/332036?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/oli-obk", "html_url": "https://github.com/oli-obk", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/oli-obk/